Name: obstructive sleep apnea
Definition: A sleep apnea that is characterized by repeated collapse and obstruction of the upper airway during sleep

Name: mixed sleep apnea
Definition: A sleep apnea that is characterized by a combination of central and obstructive sleep apnea.

Name: central sleep apnea
Definition: A sleep apnea that is characterized by a malfunction of the basic neurological controls for breathing rate and the failure to give the signal to inhale
